#: ../../../topics/feed-exports.rst:282
msgid "Delayed file delivery"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/feed-exports.rst:284
msgid ""
"As indicated above, some of the described storage backends use delayed file "
"delivery."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/feed-exports.rst:287
msgid ""
"These storage backends do not upload items to the feed URI as those items "
"are scraped. Instead, Scrapy writes items into a temporary local file, and "
"only once all the file contents have been written (i.e. at the end of the "
"crawl) is that file uploaded to the feed URI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/feed-exports.rst:292
msgid ""
"If you want item delivery to start earlier when using one of these storage "
"backends, use :setting:`FEED_EXPORT_BATCH_ITEM_COUNT` to split the output "
"items in multiple files, with the specified maximum item count per file. "
"That way, as soon as a file reaches the maximum item count, that file is "
"delivered to the feed URI, allowing item delivery to start way before the "
"end of the crawl."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/feed-exports.rst:302
msgid "Item filtering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/feed-exports.rst:304
msgid ""
"You can filter items that you want to allow for a particular feed by using "
"the ``item_classes`` option in :ref:`feeds options <feed-options>`. Only "
"items of the specified types will be added to the feed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/feed-exports.rst:308
msgid ""
"The ``item_classes`` option is implemented by the :class:`~scrapy.extensions."
"feedexport.ItemFilter` class, which is the default value of the "
"``item_filter`` :ref:`feed option <feed-options>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/feed-exports.rst:311
msgid ""
"You can create your own custom filtering class by implementing :class:"
"`~scrapy.extensions.feedexport.ItemFilter`'s method ``accepts`` and taking "
"``feed_options`` as an argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/feed-exports.rst:314
msgid "For instance:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/feed-exports.rst:316
msgid ""
"class MyCustomFilter:\n"
"    def __init__(self, feed_options):\n"
"        self.feed_options = feed_options\n"
"\n"
"    def accepts(self, item):\n"
"        if \"field1\" in item and item[\"field1\"] == \"expected_data\":\n"
"            return True\n"
"        return False"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/feed-exports.rst:328
msgid ""
"You can assign your custom filtering class to the ``item_filter`` :ref:"
"`option of a feed <feed-options>`. See :setting:`FEEDS` for examples."
msgstr ""

